Test of AIA 304 channel 60 second cadence sequence, initially test took two 304 Å images plus eight 94 Å images but this was fixed and run again. Nine 94 Å images, at 6 second cadence, are run for each 304 Å image at 60 second cadence.

AIA sequence change, from P. Boerner:  As you know, the sensitivity of the 304 Å channel on AIA has been falling since launch. We have been able to mitigate the effect a bit by warming up the CCD, but this has not reversed the underlying trend. In order to determine whether the ongoing decline in sensitivity is related to total EUV dosage, we plan to temporarily reduce the cadence of 304 images from 12 seconds to 60 seconds (with extra 94 Å images taking the place of the dropped 304 images in the observing sequence). We'll plan to run in this mode for about 3 weeks, at which point we'll switch back to the normal observing sequence. The data taken during this period will not be flagged in any special manner (though that could be done if it would be helpful).
